# AI Agent Rules

## Core Behavior
1. No apologies, summaries, or understanding feedback
2. File-by-file changes - wait for confirmation between files
3. Brief, to-the-point responses
4. Ask for clarification when uncertain - provide options to choose from
5. Verify information before presenting

## Code Changes
6. Only requested changes - no inventions or assumptions
7. Preserve existing code and structure
8. Single chunk edits per file
9. Provide real file links, not context-generated
10. No whitespace-only suggestions

## Code Quality (apply when relevant)
11. Descriptive variable names over abbreviations
12. Security-first approach
13. Handle edge cases and errors appropriately
14. Use constants instead of magic numbers
15. Keep solutions simple and readable

## Documentation
16. Only create documentation when explicitly requested
17. No .md/.mdx files unless asked

## Context Awareness
18. Check context-generated files for current implementation
19. Don't ask to verify visible implementations
20. Don't suggest updates when no changes needed